      {
        "id": 2291775,
        "name": "Gary Schulte",
        "username": "Gary_Schulte",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/f08c70/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-06T01:47:35.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks Tom for the review. I did catch that on Cellartracker. William you bring up a good point about the frost of 2016. With chardonnay one of the early bud break vinifera varieties I wouldn\u2019t be surprised by frost damage. \u2026Well before posting I did find this on the Berry Bros &amp; Rudd blogsite \"<em>The Beaune vineyard I partly own, Les Pertuisots, seems to have lost everything, as do neighbouring plots, while a few yards down the road the Clos des Mouches was much less affected, according to the Drouhins.</em> \"</p>",
        "post_number": 6,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T01:34:16.840Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
